(Fixed-size buffer truncation with format strings)

a buffer called "dst" is 8 bytes in size.

set dst to "X={1234567 add 0}".
print dst's size.
print dst.
on error print "set overflow".

copy "Y={1234567 add 0}" to dst.
print dst.
on error print "copy overflow".

clear dst.
append "Z={1234567 add 0}" to dst.
print dst.
on error print "append overflow".
